The FCC internal photos are of pretty low quality.. but this device is presumed to use RT6856.
Additional models of... *EMG2626-R10A *Keenetic Ultra are specified in the FCC test report.
Default settings are per the FCC manual. :The default IP for AP mode is specified as 192.168.1.2. :The default SSIDs may follow the pattern of '''ZyXELXXXXXX''' where '''XXXXXX''' is the last 3 octets of the respective interface's MAC address (upper case letters).
==Additional external links== *[https://forum.openwrt.org/viewtopic.php?id=46273 ''/proc/cpuinfo'' and ''/proc/meminfo'' in an '''OpenWrt Forums''' post] :128 MB RAM noted *[https://forum.openwrt.org/viewtopic.php?id=47621 Device specific thread on the '''OpenWrt Forums'''] :MX25L12845EMI-10G (16 MB) noted as Flash, W971GG6JB-25 (128 MB) noted as RAM, RTL8367RB noted as the GbE Switch, SE5003L noted as 5GHz PAs
